    {
      "para_id": "Q000996.1",
      "line_range": "1",
      "translation": "(1) For Šu-Suen , whose name was proclaimed by An , the beloved of Enlil , the king whom Enlil chose in his holy heart as the shepherd of the land and of the four quarters , the powerful king , king of Urim , king of the four quarters , his god , Ituria , governor of Ešnuna , his servant built his temple ."
    }
  ],
